OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1775268200
OL,3,CChelsea Flower Show garden to 'inspire
OL,4,Ccuriosity' gets royal seal of approval
OL,6,FCharles responds "Ah fantastic", with
OL,7,FSir David adding: "She organised
OL,8,Fthat... She chose it, so very special."
OL,10,FWhen the King asks "Does it smell?",
OL,11,FSir David quips: "It smells amazing,
OL,12,Famazing. Not as good as yours",
OL,13,Fprompting chuckles from Charles.
OL,15,FThe King's Rose is a pink and white
OL,16,Fstriped English shrub rose with a
OL,17,Fsubtle fresh red apple and rosewater
OL,18,Ffragrance, while the one named after
OL,19,FTitchmarsh is pink.
OL,26,@nD@ROUnD@_O]oD@SOUpD@gO]rD@TOUrD@cO]sD@
OL,26,AROUtD@^O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
